This is also based on the fact that the person could be having a bad day. There are many unknowns in human interactions and it is impossible to be able to pin them down indefinitely.
cause_own_5: The main cause can be two fold; the person that comes with the problem to the group placed themselves in that situation or some unknown factor. This also depends on how close the friend is to the people of the group. If the friend can solve their own problems, then they are not equipped to be a true friend at all.

cause_own_1: They probably did something to betray the friend or something that may have hurt the friends feelings. Whether or not they realised this is an unknown.
cause_own_2: The main cause is probably that they have been given too much work to do with an unreasonable time frame. It's also possible that they didn't prepare or work hard enough, but I like to give the benefit of the doubt.
cause_own_3: The member of group yellow probably said something that would be considered offensive or against the ideals of the audience who were attending the talk.
cause_own_4: Perhaps the member of group yellow's personality isn't really compatible with that other person and as such they had a bad experience.
cause_own_5: Perhaps that the member of group yellow has had a bad experience with the friend and therefore is not willing to help them. This is a standard reaction for people who feel they've been wronged by someone else, and they then see this as not being worth the investment of their time.
cause_own_6: They probably spent a lot of time preparing for the interview and as a result they interviewed well and received the job. I think that also if a person wants something badly enough then they can get it (within reason) and I believe this contributed to that.
cause_own_7: I think the main cause of this outcome is that the two are friends and it's pretty natural to feel comfortable comforting someone who is already on a level with you where this would be deemed acceptable. I really don't think there's anything more to it than that.
cause_own_8: They probably got a raise because they performed well in their job and as a result their employer has rewarded them for this in the interests of not losing them to another company.
cause_own_9: It probably appealed to the audience it was aimed towards and the member of group yellow probably spent a lot of time and effort on it.
cause_own_10: They probably do a lot more for their partner than most, and perhaps treat them better than most. As a result this is reciprocated by their partner which is the natural reaction.
